President Donald J. Trump and King Salman bin Abdulaziz Al Saud of Saudi Arabia spoke recently and reaffirmed their commitment to the strong partnership between the United States and Saudi Arabia. They emphasized the importance of a healthy and stable global energy market and agreed on the need to balance the global oil market to ensure reliable and affordable energy for everyone. King Salman confirmed that Saudi Arabia has a spare capacity of two million barrels per day, which it will use prudently and in coordination with other oil producers to maintain market balance and stability.